1) go to the directory where you want to install the toolbox and unpack
	tar -xvf pramp-0.5.0.tar.gz

2) link the launch script "bin/pramp" from a PATH-directory. for example
	cd ~/bin
	ln -s <installdirectory>/bin/pramp

3) edit the configuration file etc/pramp-gui.ini
	define a 'domain-installation-directory' - this is where pramp expects all the domain/processes
	define at least one license-server (for example: license-server-1=16090@sv02)
	define a pdfreader

checkout www.prozesskraft.de for further informations or even more tools.